Patch Set 2:

I'm not sure, but it looks like it could be better idea to import requirements.in instead of requirements.txt to avoid conflicts between libraries.
And this file probably should import the requirements.in of N2VC to, to avoid conflicts

Patch Set 2:

> Patch Set 2:
> 
> I'm not sure, but it looks like it could be better idea to import requirements.in instead of requirements.txt to avoid conflicts between libraries.
> And this file probably should import the requirements.in of N2VC to, to avoid conflicts

The whole point of pulling in requirements.txt is to identify conflicts in versions as soon as possible.  By doing it here, we will know before we even get to the stage 3 job.

Including the requirements.in of our own project is interesting, from a pip-compile perspective, but not sure how happy tox will be if we duplicate all the entries.
